<br>
We looked at each other for a brief moment, both utterly surprised. Her wings actually stopped beating for a second. Unsure of what to do, I winked at her.<br>
<br>
She bonked me on the nose with her satchel and flitted off, but did stop long enough to give me a crooked smile over her shoulder.<br>
<br>
Never hurt a faerie in my life; never did see a reason to hurt anything that didn't hurt me or mine first anyway. But I always got bonked by them and I was sure they, like every other creature I'd spent time with in this world, had a mocking nickname for me as well. Probably Badwinker Dirtynose, something like that.<br>
<br>
I don't see the little ones that often anymore, but when they do they remind me of a druidess I met once upon a time, an ethereal creature who seemed, to me at least, to be a kind of avatar of joy...<br>
<br>
I took the glowing skullcap from my head and tucked it away, walking homeward in the heavy night of the Faydark. And my way was lit distantly by the glow of far off faeriekin.<br>
***<br>
... the wolf drifted out of the darkness, the faerielight catching in hisfur. His eyes glowed, and when he saw me, he smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;I realize this is going to make me seem very unmanly,&quot; I said to No Moon ashe trotted over to me, &quot;but sometimes I wish you were really here, so I could<br>
throw my arms around you.&quot;<br>
<br>
The wolf just grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;What's bothering you, boy?&quot; the ghost of my oldest friend said.<br>
<br>
I shrugged.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dunno,&quot; I muttered. I paused, took a mint leaf out of my pouch, tucked it in my mouth. &quot;This is a great big world, No Moon.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And you're alone in it. That's not good, boy.&quot;<br>
<br>
I shrugged again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Should go back to Everfrost, lad. The wolves there like you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, really? And what do they call me? Let me guess -- Dulltooth Badhunter?&quot;<br>
<br>
No Moon shook his head. The gesture was surprisingly disconcerting on a wolf.<br>
<br>
&quot;Brother Sadeyes. They call you Brother Sadeyes.&quot;<br>
<br>
Something twinged inside me, like a broken string, a quick, sharp pain instantly gone. My eyes welled up and I turned away from No Moon, wishing I could still pat his fur, wishing he was still at my side teaching me.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where are you,&quot; I asked, trying to change the subject, &quot;when you're not here with me?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You know I can't tell you that.&quot; He paused, rested his head on his paws.&quot;But it's a happy place, Lest-ye-forget. It's a happy place and I am notalone. I just come visit you when I know you're not alright.&quot;<br>
<br>
I knelt down as close as I could to No Moon without touching him, withoutbreaking the illusion that he was alive.<br>
<br>
&quot;I wish you were still here,&quot; I whispered.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know, boy. I know.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 685<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/17/02 6:09:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=420.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: by faerielight</span><hr size=1> (( Lest has a very sad life!  Excellent story, excellent! *sniffle* )) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lest>Lest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/02 2:07:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=420.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> much thanks</span><hr size=1> (/OOC Thank you for the feedback, and sorry for the sniffles... I've built up such a sad pathos for Lest I feel like I should create a carefree, happy-smiley secondary character just to prove I'm not morose...) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=420.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=420.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=420.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> <